    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 power plant. This naturally aspirated 3.2L inline-six utilizes individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS variable valve timing to produce a linear power band peaking at 7,900 RPM. The drivetrain features the desirable Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M-Differential lock for optimal torque distribution. This example has undergone essential preventative maintenance, including rod bearing replacement and a comprehensive subframe reinforcement to address known E46 chassis fatigue. The suspension geometry remains true, providing the communicative feedback and neutral handling balance synonymous with the M-division. A technically sound driver\u2019s car optimized for performance consistency.",
